ce:section.ce:para:
Based on the C54H18 graphene model, the effects of different oxygen-containing functional groups (carboxyl, hydroxyl, and epoxy) on the monolayer graphene structure were systematically investigated, including its aggregation behavior. Using DFT calculations, the results (Fig. 1
                            and Table 1
                           ) visually demonstrated the structural changes and aggregation characteristics of the GQDs with various functional group modifications, therefore providing theoretical support for understanding the relationship between structure and performance.
